\sum_{n=1}^\infty f^{(n)}(x)\frac{x^n(1-x)^n}{n!}\;\;\text{ converges to }\;\;f(x+x(1-x)) - f(x)
\begin{align} f(x+x(1-x))-f(x)  &= \frac{x + x(1-x)}{\log(1 - (x+x(1-x)))} - \frac{x}{\log(1-x)}\\ &= \frac{2x - x^2}{2\log(1-x)} - \frac{x}{\log(1-x)}\\ &= - \frac{x^2}{2\log(1-x)}\\ &= -\frac{x}{2}f(x) \end{align}
